'''多株B細胞反應'''（{{lang-en|polyclonal B cell response}}）是一種[[哺乳類|哺乳類]][[後天免疫系統|後天免疫系統]]所表現的自然免疫反應。它確保多[[細胞株_(B細胞)|株]][[B細胞|B細胞]]能辨識單獨[[抗原|抗原]]，進而攻擊抗原被抗體辨識或結合的部分，即[[抗原決定位|抗原決定位]]（{{lang-en|epitopes}}）<ref name="goldsby3">{{cite book | last = Goldsby | first = Richard | coauthors = Kindt, TJ; Osborne, BA; Janis Kuby| title = Immunology | url = https://archive.org/details/immunologyfifthe00gold | edition = Fifth | publisher = W. H. Freeman and Company | date = 2003 | location = New York | pages = [https://archive.org/details/immunologyfifthe00gold/page/n57 57]–75 | chapter = Antigens (Chapter 3) | isbn = 0-07167-4947-5 |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | title = Definition of Polyclonal from MedicineNet.com | publisher = Webster's New World Medical Dictionary | date =  | url = http://www.medterms.com/script/main/art.asp?articlekey=20127 | accessdate = 2008-05-03 | language = en | archive-date = 2012-08-07 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20120807034926/http://www.medterms.com/script/main/art.asp?articlekey=20127 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。

在正常的免疫反應中，免疫系統能辨識[[病原體|病原體]]（如：[[細菌|細菌]]）的特定部位為外來物（非自我），進而消滅或有效中和病原體，以降低其潛在的破壞性。這種能被辨識的物質稱為[[抗原|抗原]]。免疫系統有多種對付抗原的途徑；其中一種免疫機制稱為[[體液免疫|體液免疫]]，即由B細胞製造[[抗體|抗體]]對抗抗原。抗體具可溶性，能免去抗原和B細胞之間的直接接觸。

抗原通常是一種巨大而構造複雜的物質，而單一抗體只能和抗原的特定微小部位結合。因此，免疫系統通常由多種不同的B細胞製造出大量不同的抗體，對同一個抗原執行免疫反應。細胞株（{{lang-en|clone}}）是指一群由單一母細胞所產生的細胞，故名為「多株」（{{lang-en|polyclonal}}）<ref name="url">{{cite book |last= Frank |first= Steven A. |title= Immunology and Evolution of Infectious Disease |url= http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/bookshelf/br.fcgi?book=infdis&part=A22#A23|accessdate= 2008-06-23 |year= 2002 |publisher= Princeton University |isbn= 0-0691-09595-7 |pages= 33–56 |chapter= Specificity and Cross-Reactivity (Chapter 4) |language=en}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url = http://www.etymonline.com/index.php?search=clone&searchmode=none |title = Etymology of "clone" |publisher = Online etymology dictionary |accessdate = 2008-06-26 |language = en |archive-date = 2017-02-15 |archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20170215232438/http://www.etymonline.com/index.php?search=clone&searchmode=none |dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal | last =Bansal | first =R.K. | year =2005 | title =Reproductive Cloning-An Act Of Human Rights Violation | journal =Journal of Indian Association of Forensic Medicine | volume =27 | issue =3 | publisher =Indian Association of Forensic Medicine | pages =971–973 | url =http://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache:hYkYyeFNZEgJ:medind.nic.in/jal/t05/i3/jalt05i3p180.pdf+Klon+clone+sprout&hl=en&ct=clnk&cd=8&gl=in&client=firefox-a | accessdate =2008-06-23 | language =en | author = | archive-url =https://web.archive.org/web/20170323045634/http://webcache.googleusercontent.com/search?q=cache%3AhYkYyeFNZEgJ%3Amedind.nic.in%2Fjal%2Ft05%2Fi3%2Fjalt05i3p180.pdf+Klon+clone+sprout&hl=en&ct=clnk&cd=8&gl=in&client=firefox-a | archive-date =2017-03-23 | dead-url =yes }}</ref>。在多株反應中製造的抗體稱為[[多株抗體|多株抗體]]。異質的多株抗體和[[單株抗體|單株抗體]]不同；後者彼此間構造完全相同，只針對同一個抗原決定位產生反應，較具有專一性。

多株反應能更有效地對抗病原體，讓免疫系統更具有優勢；然而，由於免疫系統也可能對抗寄主本身製造的分子物質，它同時提高了發展出特定自體免疫疾病的機會。

